Spending on contactless cards more than trebled last year to a record £2.32billion, figures show.

Users made ten contactless payments every second in 2014 as they entered mainstream use. It means they were used a total of 319.2million times, the UK Cards Association reports.

The steep rise has prompted the spending limit on the cards to be increased to £30 from September this year. 

